How can I generate a heat map of a matrix in MATLAB and export it as a PDF file? Can you provide an example of such code?
Sure! Here's an example MATLAB code that generates a heat map of a matrix and exports it as a PDF file:
```matlab
% Create a random matrix
matrix = randn(10);
% Generate the heat map
heatmap(matrix);
% Set the title and color bar label
title('Heat Map of Random Matrix');
colorbar('FontSize', 12, 'FontWeight', 'bold', 'TickDirection', 'out');
% Export the heat map as a PDF file
print('heatmap.pdf', '-dpdf');
```
This code first creates a random matrix using the `randn` function. It then generates a heat map of the matrix using the `heatmap` function. The code sets the title of the heat map and the label of the color bar using the `title` and `colorbar` functions. Finally, the code exports the heat map as a PDF file using the `print` function.
To run this code, simply copy and paste it into a MATLAB script and run it in the MATLAB environment. The output will be a PDF file named `heatmap.pdf` that contains the generated heat map.

