You can use the AVG function in SQL to find the average age of all employees in a company. Here is an example SQL query:
SELECT AVG(age) FROM employees;
In this query, 'age' is the name of the column that contains the ages of each employee, and 'employees' is the name of the table that contains all employee data. The AVG function calculates the average of all the values in the age column and returns the result as a single value.
